Entry and borders
See Entry requirements to find out what you will need to do when you arrive in Wallis and Futuna.
Travel in Wallis and Futuna
To travel within or to transit through French Overseas Territories, you should complete an Attestation de déplacement dérogatoire to certify your reason for travel. You can carry a physical copy or an electronic version of this ‘attestation’ (declaration). You should complete this declaration before starting your journey.
For French Overseas Territories, this declaration does not replace the requirement for an travel certificate, see Entry requirements. Further information is available on the Ministry of Interior webpage.
The French Government outlined new measures on 16 March to stem the spread of coronavirus, which also apply to the French Overseas Territories. This included confining people to their homes except for outings for specific purposes effective from midday 17 March 2020. The local Prefecture website will have details of any further local restriction.
